                <h1>NVIDIA: A Brief History of Innovation</h1>
                <p>NVIDIA was founded in 1993 by Jensen Huang, Chris Malachowsky, and Curtis Priem. The company gained prominence with the introduction of the RIVA series of graphics cards in the late '90s and revolutionized gaming with the GeForce 256 in 1999. NVIDIA has since expanded into AI, deep learning, and autonomous vehicles, solidifying its tech leadership.</p>
